At [Japan Subculture Research Center](http://www.japansubculture.com/)‘s blog,
Richard Orange and [Ikuru Kuwajima](http://www.ikurukuwajima.com/) tell [ the
story](http://www.japansubculture.com/2011/02/the-last-japanese-man-remaining-
in-kazakhstan-a-kafkian-tale-of-the-plight-of-a-japanese-pow-in-the-soviet-
union/) [en] of “one Japanese POW trapped in the Soviet Union after the end of
the Second World War.”

